Reasoning: We inspected the workbook and found it has one sheet with 3 columns: A (Item), B (Preorder Total / descriptor), and C (numeric values). The user wants a formula that, instead of counting rows where column B equals a value (e.g., "TV"), sums the corresponding values in column C (the cell immediately to the right). The appropriate Excel formula is `=SUMIFS(C:C,B:B,"TV")`. To give the user a flexible per‑row version we can also place a helper column D that returns the value from C when B matches the target, using `=IF(B2="TV",C2,0)` and copy it down. We'll add a header in D1, fill D2:D<max_row> with the IF formula, and also place a total sum in the last row+1 (e.g., D<max_row+1>) using `=SUM(D2:D<max_row>)`. This meets the requirement without overwriting existing data, uses only existing columns plus a new column D, and works with LibreOffice. After saving, we will recalculate the workbook to ensure formulas evaluate.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter

# Paths
input_path = input_spreadsheet
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/"
output_path = output_dir + "1_50796_init.xlsx"

# Load workbook (preserve formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]

# Determine dimensions
max_row = ws.max_row
max_col = ws.max_column

# Add header for new column D (index 4)
header_cell = ws.cell(row=1, column=4)
header_cell.value = "Sum if TV"

# Fill column D with IF formula per row
for r in range(2, max_row + 1):
    # Formula: =IF(B{r}="TV",C{r},0)
    ws.cell(row=r, column=4).value = f'=IF(B{r}="TV",C{r},0)'

# Add a total sum at the row after the last data row
total_row = max_row + 1
ws.cell(row=total_row, column=4).value = f'=SUM(D2:D{max_row})'
ws.cell(row=total_row, column=3).value = "Total TV"

# Ensure output directory exists
import os
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Save workbook
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas
recalc_result = await recalculate(output_path)
print("Recalculate result:", recalc_result)

# Reload with data_only to verify
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check[ws_check.sheetnames[0]]
# Print the total cell value
print("Total TV (cell D{}):".format(total_row), ws_check.cell(row=total_row, column=4).value)
